---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [{"href":"#quickstart","label":"Quickstart"},{"href":"#what","label":"What's in the box"},{"href":"#faq","label":"FAQ"},{"href":"angles.html","label":"All angles"}];
const navCta = {"href":"#demo","label":"Technical walkthrough →"};
---

<Layout variant="developers">
  <Nav variant="developers" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">For insurance engineering teams</span>
    <h1>Ship AI agents <em>compliance won't fight.</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Phidea is a governed MCP server that wraps your insurance tools — retrieval,
      pricing, claims, policy servicing — behind one tool call with grounded
      citations, price-accurate quoting, and staged guardrails built in.
      Drop it into Claude Desktop, Cursor, or any MCP client.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-primary">Book a 30-min walkthrough →</a>
      <a href="#quickstart" class="btn btn-ghost">See the quickstart</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span><strong>Python</strong> SDK · <strong>MCP</strong> stdio</span>
      <span><strong>Open</strong> reference agent (FR auto)</span>
      <span><strong>Policy-as-code</strong> guardrails</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="what">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">What's in the box</div>
      <h2>One governed surface over the primitives you already have.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Most insurance AI pilots die because the LLM orchestrates raw tools
        directly and the guardrail layer sits off to the side. Phidea collapses
        that: there is one tool, it is governed end-to-end, and the governance
        travels with the tool.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">01 · Governed Triage</div>
        <h3>One tool call. Full staged guardrails.</h3>
        <p>
          A FastMCP server exposes a single high-level tool: <code>ask_insurance_assistant</code>.
          Every call runs pre-flight (PII, moderation), input (jailbreak,
          off-topic), and output (PII scrub, grounding, price accuracy)
          guardrails. Raw primitives are not exposed directly, so the client
          LLM cannot bypass the pipeline.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>FastMCP / stdio — drops into Claude Desktop, Cursor, agent SDKs</li>
          <li>OpenAI Agents SDK underneath, any model provider above</li>
          <li>Policy pack system (insurance-core + fr-acpr + auto-lob overlays)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <pre class="code"><span class="c"># ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</span>
<span class="k">&#123;</span>
  <span class="s">"mcpServers"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span>
    <span class="s">"phidea-insurance"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span>
      <span class="s">"command"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="s">"/path/.venv/bin/python"</span><span class="k">,</span>
      <span class="s">"args"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">[</span><span class="s">"-m"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"agent.mcp_server"</span><span class="k">]</span><span class="k">,</span>
      <span class="s">"env"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span> <span class="s">"OPENAI_API_KEY"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="s">"sk-..."</span> <span class="k">&#125;</span>
    <span class="k">&#125;</span>
  <span class="k">&#125;</span>
<span class="k">&#125;</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">02 · Policy Packs</div>
        <h3>Jurisdiction rules as runtime policies.</h3>
        <p>
          <code>insurance-core-policy</code> plus overlay packages for each
          jurisdiction and line of business. Advice-seeking classifier,
          groundedness check, price-accuracy check, disclaimer injection,
          vulnerable-customer detector, jurisdiction resolver — each a separate
          guardrail, independently versioned, independently tuneable.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>pip-installable policy packages</li>
          <li>Staged pipeline: pre-flight → input → output</li>
          <li>Eval dataset + precision/recall per guardrail</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <pre class="code"><span class="c"># policy_packs/insurance_core/config.json</span>
<span class="k">&#123;</span>
  <span class="s">"version"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="s">"1.2.0"</span><span class="k">,</span>
  <span class="s">"pre_flight"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span>
    <span class="s">"guardrails"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">[</span><span class="s">"pii_detect"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"moderation"</span><span class="k">]</span>
  <span class="k">&#125;</span><span class="k">,</span>
  <span class="s">"input"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span>
    <span class="s">"guardrails"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">[</span><span class="s">"jailbreak"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"off_topic"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"advice_seeking"</span><span class="k">]</span>
  <span class="k">&#125;</span><span class="k">,</span>
  <span class="s">"output"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">&#123;</span>
    <span class="s">"guardrails"</span><span class="k">:</span> <span class="k">[</span><span class="s">"pii_scrub"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"groundedness"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"price_accuracy"</span><span class="k">,</span> <span class="s">"idd_disclaimer"</span><span class="k">]</span>
  <span class="k">&#125;</span>
<span class="k">&#125;</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <div class="feature-label">03 · Open Reference Agent</div>
        <h3>A working French auto insurance agent you can run today.</h3>
        <p>
          A reference implementation ships as the public test case:
          <code>insurance-agent-v1</code>. Real IPIDs (MAIF VAM, AXA Mon Auto).
          ChromaDB retrieval. Governed pipeline. MCP stdio server. Smoke tests.
          Adapt it to your LOB, your carrier, your jurisdiction.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>One specialist (QuoteAgent) — extend to claims, servicing, renewals</li>
          <li>Policy pack overlays for US states land next</li>
          <li>Eval dataset of adversarial + benign queries included</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-visual">
        <pre class="code"><span class="c"># quickstart</span>
git clone github.com/phidea/insurance-agent-v1
cd insurance-agent-v1
python -m venv .venv <span class="k">&&</span> source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .

<span class="c"># one-time: ingest the IPID corpus</span>
python -m grounding.indexer

<span class="c"># run as an MCP server</span>
python -m agent.mcp_server
<span class="n">==> serving stdio on phidea-insurance</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="quickstart">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Architecture</div>
      <h2>How the pipeline fits together.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        The client LLM sees one tool. Underneath, every turn runs a staged
        pipeline that a compliance team can audit.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-grid">
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">01 / Pre-flight</div>
        <h3>Before anything touches the model.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">PII detection (block), moderation. Fast, cheap, fail-closed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">02 / Input + Agent</div>
        <h3>Jailbreak, off-topic, advice-seeking.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">The triage agent routes to a specialist. Tools run grounded retrieval and deterministic pricing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="how-step">
        <div class="num">03 / Output</div>
        <h3>Groundedness, price accuracy, disclaimer.</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">Factual claims must resolve to retrieved passages. Numbers must match the pricing API exactly. IDD disclaimer appended.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
      <h2>For engineering.</h2>
    </div>
    <details><summary>Why MCP and not a REST API?</summary><p>MCP is the surface every serious agent runtime now speaks — Claude Desktop, Cursor, OpenAI Agents, LangGraph. Ship once, run everywhere. The server also exposes a REST adapter for clients that aren't MCP-native.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can we self-host?</summary><p>Yes. The reference agent runs locally. Production deploy is a container; VPC / on-prem options exist for carriers with that requirement.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Which model providers are supported?</summary><p>OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Mistral, and any OpenAI-compatible endpoint. The policy pipeline is provider-agnostic.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What about latency?</summary><p>Pre-flight + input guardrails add ~50ms typical. Groundedness check adds ~100ms. Price-accuracy check is synchronous against the pricing tool. End-to-end target is sub-2s for a typical Q&amp;A turn.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is the reference agent open source?</summary><p>The <code>insurance-agent-v1</code> reference agent is released under a permissive license. Policy packs and the observability gateway are source-available under a carrier-EULA — repo access on request.</p></details>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="demo">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta-panel">
      <h2>Book a technical walkthrough.</h2>
      <p>Thirty minutes. We'll run the reference agent live, step through the policy pipeline, and map it to one of your use cases.</p>
      <form class="demo" action="https://phidea-forms.vercel.app/api/lead" method="POST">
        <input type="hidden" name="variant" value="developers" />
        <input type="text" name="carrier" placeholder="Company" required />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Work email" required />
        <button type="submit">Book walkthrough →</button>
      </form>
      <div class="cta-foot">For CTOs, Heads of AI, and platform leads. We'll share the repo link on the call.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
